			<description><![CDATA[<p>
What you&rsquo;ll do:</p>
<p>
&bull; Lead. You will be in charge of cultivating a hacker/get-shit-done culture and making sure that it stays. You will be a cornerstone of our organization responsible for setting strategic directions for the engineering team by guiding technology decisions and developing tech talent.</p>
<p>
&bull; Architect. You will determine the long-term architecture of our platform and be responsible for implementing the company&rsquo;s product development vision.&nbsp; You have deep technical knowledge of Ruby on Rails/MySQL and scaling an app to millions of users.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
&bull; Hack. You should have a passion for clean code and be comfortable with test-driven development, quick turnarounds, rapid deployments, and quickly responding to surges. You love to code and solve complex problems.</p>
<p>
About You:</p>
<p>
&bull; Got Mad Skillz. You have scaled apps to be able to efficiently handle millions of actions per month.&nbsp; You have first hand experience deploying and scaling multiple servers using one or more of the following: Capistrano, Chef, EC2. You have the ability to analyze inefficiencies in server/application using tools like Nagios &amp; New Relic and implement more efficient/elegant solutions.</p>
<p>
&bull; Know the Tools. You&rsquo;re not afraid of MySQL replication &amp; optimization, RESTful JSON APIs, eCommerce APIs, HAML/SASS, Memcache, Delayed Job/Resque, Redis, Sphinx, OAuth2, Git and test-driven development.&nbsp; You&rsquo;ve worked with Heroku.</p>
<p>
&bull; The 1:10 Engineer. You go above and beyond because hacking is a part of who you are.&nbsp; You acknowledge that there&rsquo;s a time for everything and aren&#39;t dogmatic about any one methodology: You realize there&#39;s a time for being lean, agile and user-centered, but also a time for trusting your intuition, vision and heart.</p>
<p>
Big pluses:<br />
&bull; Experience developing for large-scale ecommerce (integrated shopping cart, PayPal API, etc).<br />
&bull; Experience bringing a SaaS mail system in-house.</p>
<p>
Benefits + Perks:<br />
&bull; Salary + Bonus: Competitive base + potential bonus based on experience and performance.<br />
&bull; Equity: Generous equity stake for the right candidate.<br />
&bull; Dream Setup: Whatever equipment you need to be at your best, up to $3000.<br />
&bull; Super Flex Time: Run errands as needed, just get your stuff done.<br />
&bull; Free Food/Drinks: We&rsquo;ll stock the cabinets and the fridge for you.<br />
&bull; Hack Days: Two days per quarter to work on any Company-related project you want.<br />
&bull; Location: Our office is across from the Beach&hellip;take a jog to clear your mind!</p>
<p>
Apply:<br />
&bull; Send an email and cover letter to josh@stacksocial.com with links to all applicable pages that you have (i.e. your portfolio, blog, LinkedIn, twitter, etc.).</p>
